        <div class="con">
          <div class="nlst">
            <h3>
              <div class="note-toggle rr">
                <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/11149606/" class="note-unfolder">展开</a>
                <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="note-folder">收起</a>
              </div>
              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/11149606/" class="">第225页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/maynepaddy/" class=" " title="Mayne Katze">Mayne Katze</a>
                (無產階級餵貓騎士)
              
                <span class="allstar50" title="力荐"></span>
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="11149606">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <div class="ll">
                    <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/11149606/"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/small/public/p11149606-1.jpg"></a>
                  </div>
                  <span class="">伊莉莎白汤普森




Scotland for Ever! by Lady Elizabeth Butler
Scotland Forever! is an 1881 painting by Lady Butler depicting the start of the charge by the Royal Scots Greys at the Battle of Waterloo in 1815. In actuality, it appears that Scots Greys never started the charge at a gallop, due to the broken ground, and instead advanced at a quick walk. The painting is now housed at the Leeds ...</span>
                  &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/11149606/">(<span class="">7回应</span>)</a>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2011-02-06 11:19</span>
                  
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="">2人喜欢</span>
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                伊莉莎白汤普森<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><div class="middle"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p11149606-1.jpg" alt="Elizabeth Thompson, Lady Butler (3 November 1846 – 2 October 1933) "><br><span class="pic-title">Elizabeth Thompson, Lady Butler (3 November 1846 – 2 October 1933) </span></div><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><div class="middle"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p11149606-2.jpg" alt="Scotland Forever （苏格兰灰骑兵）"><br><span class="pic-title">Scotland Forever （苏格兰灰骑兵）</span></div>
Scotland for Ever! by Lady Elizabeth Butler<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Scotland Forever! is an 1881 painting by Lady Butler depicting the start of the charge by the Royal Scots Greys at the Battle of Waterloo in 1815. In actuality, it appears that Scots Greys never started the charge at a gallop, due to the broken ground, and instead advanced at a quick walk. The painting is now housed at the Leeds Art Gallery, having been one of its earliest acquisitions, a gift from Colonel Thomas Walter Harding (1843–1927) [1]. It was also an inspiration for the depiction of the same charge in the film Waterloo.[citation needed]<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>The regiment was based at Piershill Barracks in Restalrig, Edinburgh.
<div class="middle"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p11149606-3.jpg" alt="Remnants of an army   William Brydon外科助理，英军自喀布尔向贾拉拉巴德撤退时的幸存者"><br><span class="pic-title">Remnants of an army   William Brydon外科助理，英军自喀布尔向贾拉拉巴德撤退时的幸存者</span></div><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>'Remnants of an Army' by Elizabeth Butler portraying William Brydon arriving at the gates of Jalalabad as the only survivor of a 16,500 strong evacuation from Kabul in January 1842. This is a better copy of a file in Commons (this image is in the public domain due to its age).<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>Scanned copy of the painting in the Tate Gallery
<a rel="nofollow" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Brydon" target="_blank">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Brydon</a>
<div class="middle"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p11149606-4.jpg" alt="&quot;The 28th Regiment at Quatre Bras&quot;"><br><span class="pic-title">&quot;The 28th Regiment at Quatre Bras&quot;</span></div>
The painting portrays the 28th (North Gloucestershire) Regiment of Foot, of the British Army, on June 16, 1815, at the Battle of Quatre Bras. The battle, part of the Waterloo Campaign of the Hundred Days, was just two days prior to the Battle of Waterloo. The regiment held off attacks from French cavalry at Quatre Bras. Thompson shows the regiment formed in a square withstanding attacks, at approximately 17:00, from Polish Lancers and cuirassier veterans led by Marshal Ney.
<a rel="nofollow" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_28th_Regiment_at_Quatre_Bras" target="_blank">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_28th_Regiment_at_Quatre_Bras</a><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><div class="middle"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p11149606-5.jpg" alt="&quot;The Defence of Rorke's Drift&quot;"><br><span class="pic-title">&quot;The Defence of Rorke's Drift&quot;</span></div>
a battle in the Anglo-Zulu War. The defence of the mission station of Rorke's Drift, under the command of Lieutenant John Chard of the Royal Engineers, immediately followed the British Army's defeat at the Battle of Isandlwana on 22 January 1879, and continued into the following day, 23 January. 
<a rel="nofollow" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Rorke%27s_Drift" target="_blank">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Rorke%27s_Drift</a><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><div class="middle"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p11149606-6.jpg" alt="&quot;Floreat Etona!&quot; 布尔战争"><br><span class="pic-title">&quot;Floreat Etona!&quot; 布尔战争</span></div>
<a rel="nofollow" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Elwes_%28British_Army_officer%29" target="_blank">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Elwes_%28British_Army_officer%29</a>
                  <div class="col-rec-con clearfix">
                    







